<TITLE> MTV developing thrills, chills </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LOS ANGELES, June 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Following the pickup of its first scripted series in five years, MTV is developing a dark thriller and a campy horror. 'Darius' explores the dark, secret life of an all-American teenager, while 'Cheerleader Camp' is described as 'Heathers' meets 'Scream.' The titles for both are tentative. 'Darius' would employ a combination of traditional narrative and multimedia elements, said Tony DiSanto, executive vp series development and programming at MTV. "It's a multimedia approach to storytelling and will allow us cool extensions into other platforms," he said. "It's also a tonal shift for us as well, touching on the thriller genre, and I love being able to play in different areas." He described 'Cheerleader Camp' as "something that's really new and different and fun." The lifestyle network in February picked up 'Kaya,' a half-hour music-themed dra
